\begin_inset Formula $M=\left(X_{\left(1\right)}+X_{\left(n\right)}\right)/2$
\end_inset

, so that we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{flalign*}
\mathcal{B} & =\left\{ \left(r,m\right):r=v-u,m=\left(u+v\right)/2,\left(u,v\right)\in\mathcal{A}\right\} .
